28/11/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The prime ministers of countries in the Central European Initiative completed a meeting in Sofia on Tuesday (November 27th) with a joint declaration pledging to unite efforts aimed at guaranteeing regional peace, stability and development.
Boosting democratic institutions and efforts to strengthen market economies were cited as top priorities.
The leaders also stressed the need for a long-term solution to the Kosovo status issue.
Discussions about the province's future prompted a brief walkout by members of the Serbian delegation.
(Vecer, Koha Jone, Top-Channel - 28/11/07;
A1, Actualno, Kanal 5, MRT, Novinite, RFI, Dnevnik, Dir.bg, Albanian Prime Minister website, AP - 27/11/07)
